ORNI 47 and ORNI 37 are sometimes referred to individually as a "Co-Tenant" or collectively as the "Co-Tenants," which terms shall include their permitted successors, permitted assignees or nominees and shall also include any party that executes a joinder agreement pursuant to Section 8.2(b) below. Each of ORNI 47, ORNI 37 and the Shared Facilities Manager is referred in this Agreement individually as a Party and collectively they are referred to in this Agreement as the Parties. Certain capitalized terms used in this Agreement are given defined meanings in Appendix A attached hereto. R E C I T A L S: A. ORNI 47 and ORNI 37 will be holders, as tenants in common, of that certain grant of right-of-way from the United States Bureau of Land Management identified as NVN-090685 (the "Undivided Transmission Line Grant"). B. The Undivided Transmission Line Grant will provide for undivided interests of the Co-Tenants in the transmission line right of way over the real property more particularly described in Exhibit A (collectively, the "Shared Premises"). C. ORNI 47 owns and operates a geothermal electric power generation project (the "Don A. Campbell 1 Project"), which Don A. Campbell 1 Project is located in Mineral County, Nevada. D. ORNI 37 is developing and will own and operate a geothermal electric power generation project (the Don A. Campbell 2 Project ), which Don A. Campbell 2 Project is located in Mineral County, Nevada. E. ORNI 47 designed, procured, constructed, and installed the Initial Shared Facilities at its expense, as described in this Agreement. F. The electric energy output of the Don A. Campbell 1 Project is sold to the Southern California Public Power Authority ( SCPPA ) under the Don A. Campbell 1 PPA and the electric energy output of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project is to be sold to SCPPA under the Proposed Don A. Campbell 2 PPA. G. ORNI 47 and ORNI 37 each desire to obtain an undivided interest in certain of the Shared Facilities in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, to enable each of them to jointly use the Shared Facilities in connection with the development, installation and operation of their Projects, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement as approved by SCPPA pursuant to the Don A. Campbell 1 PPA. H. The Co-Tenants and Sierra Pacific Power Company d/b/a NV Energy are entering into the First Amended and Restated Standard Large Generator Interconnection Agreement, as approved by SCPPA ( FA&R LGIA ). I. The Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager are entering into the Large Generator Interconnection Co-Tenancy Agreement, as approved by SCPPA ( LGI Co-Tenancy Agreement ). J. The Co-Tenants wish to set forth herein the rights and obligations of the Co-Tenants with respect to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. K. The Shared Facilities Manager has experience in the operation and maintenance of improvements, equipment and facilities similar to the Shared Facilities. L. The Co-Tenants desire to engage the Shared Facilities Manager to operate and maintain the Shared Facilities and the Shared Facilities Manager desires to operate and maintain the Shared Facilities for the benefit of the Co-Tenants in accordance with the terms hereof. NOW, THEREFORE, in consideration of the mutual promises contained herein, and for other good and valuable consideration, the receipt and adequacy of which are hereby acknowledged by the Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager, the Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager agree as follows: ARTICLE 1 SHARED FACILITIES; EFFECTIVE DATE 1.1 Partial Conveyance of and Interests in Shared Facilities. (a) ORNI 47 has procured, installed and constructed, along and within the Shared Premises, (i) a 120 kV transmission line for the transmission of electricity, connecting the Don A. Campbell 1 Project to the Sierra Pacific Power Company d/b/a NV Energy Excelsior 120 kV Substation, including towers, poles, crossarms, guy lines and anchors (the Initial Shared Facilities ); provided, however, that the Initial Shared Facilities do not include the Don A. Campbell 1 Project Facilities. After giving effect to the transfers hereunder, each Co-Tenant has an equal undivided ownership interest in each segment of the Initial Shared Facilities. (b) Upon and subject to the terms, conditions, restrictions and reservations set forth herein, each Co-Tenant hereby transfers and conveys unto the other Co-Tenant, as is and without warranty of any kind or nature, except as to title by, through or under such grantor, an undivided ownership interest in and to any and all of the Shared Facilities, now owned or hereafter acquired, while at the same time reserving to itself an undivided ownership interest in and to such Shared Facilities. Each of the Co-Tenants shall own, hold, and utilize and retain the right to utilize its Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities, as described in Exhibit B attached hereto, in accordance with the terms of this Agreement. (c) As of the Effective Date, the applicable Proportionate Share of each Co-Tenant holding an Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities as a result of the conveyance herein is set forth on Exhibit B until adjusted pursuant to the terms hereof. (d) The Co-Tenants acknowledge and agree that the Don A. Campbell 2 Project is not currently an electricity generating project. Therefore, in the event that the Don A. Campbell 2 Project is constructed and operated and ORNI 37 utilizes its rights to the Shared Facilities, the Co-Tenants will readjust ORNI 37's Proportionate Share as set forth in Exhibit B pursuant to this Agreement. 1.2 Operation and Maintenance of the Shared Facilities. Operation, maintenance, replacement and repair of the Shared Facilities shall be the responsibility of the Shared Facilities Manager, and shall include those responsibilities listed in Exhibit D; provided that in the case of each Project, the Shared Facilities Manager shall carry out its responsibilities subject to and in accordance with the applicable terms and provisions of the Don A. Campbell 1 PPA or the Proposed Don A. Campbell 2 PPA, as applicable. The costs and expenses incurred to maintain the Shared Facilities shall be incurred and shared in accordance with Article 2 below. 1.3 Access to the Shared Facilities. Each Participating Co-Tenant and, subject to any applicable requirements or limitations in the applicable loan documents, any Secured Party of such Co-Tenant, shall have access to the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities (i) for inspection of such Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, (ii) for maintenance of such Shared Facilities not performed by the Shared Facilities Manager in the time permitted by Section 9.2 hereof, and (iii) for maintenance or repair of the Shared Facilities in the event of an Emergency and the failure or unavailability of the Shared Facilities Manager or its representatives to respond timely to such Emergency; provided that such Co-Tenant shall indemnify the other Co-Tenant from all third party claims resulting from such inspection, maintenance or repair undertaken by such Co-Tenant or such Co-Tenant's Secured Party. Notwithstanding the foregoing, except in the event of an Emergency, the Co-Tenant or its Secured Party shall give the Shared Facilities Manager and the other Co-Tenant prior written notice of its intent to enter upon the Shared Premises, and the Co-Tenant or its Secured Party, as applicable, shall follow all written safety and security procedures adopted by the Shared Facilities Manager with respect to the Shared Premises and Shared Facilities. 1.4 No Interference. A Co-Tenant s use of any Shared Facilities shall not in any way unreasonably interfere with the use and enjoyment by the other Co-Tenant of its respective rights in the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises or under this Agreement or the use and enjoyment by ORNI 47 of the Don A. Campbell 1 Project Facilities, except as expressly set forth herein. 1.5 Replacement of Components of Shared Facilities. (a) Without prior notice to and consent of the Participating Co-Tenants, the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right to replace any component of a Shared Facility with a Qualified Replacement Component (i) if the cost of the Qualified Replacement Component (including installation) is less than Fifty Thousand Dollars ($50,000), (ii) if such replacement, and the cost thereof, is included in the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget, or (iii) if required in the event of an Emergency. Notice of such replacement shall be given by the Shared Facilities Manager to the Participating Co-Tenants as soon as reasonably practicable after the replacement thereof. (b) Except as otherwise permitted by Section 1.5(a), the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide notice (the "Replacement Notice") in writing to the Participating Co-Tenants of (i) any component of a Shared Facility that needs replacement, (ii) the proposed replacement component (the "Proposed Replacement Component"), which shall be a Qualified Replacement Component, and (iii) the estimated cost (including installation) thereof. If the Participating Co-Tenant holding fifty percent (50%) or greater of the Proportionate Shares approves the Proposed Replacement Component, the Shared Facilities Manager shall replace such Shared Facility component with the Proposed Replacement Component. If the Participating Co-Tenant(s) holding fifty percent (50%) or greater of the Proportionate Shares fail(s) to approve the Proposed Replacement Component within fifteen (15) days of receipt of the Replacement Notice, the other Participating Co-Tenant may propose a commercially reasonable alternative replacement component (the "Alternative Replacement Component") within thirty (30) days of receipt of the Replacement Notice, and, if the Participating Co-Tenant(s) holding more than fifty percent (50%) of the Proportionate Shares approve the Alternative Replacement Component, the Shared Facilities Manager shall proceed with the installation of the Alternative Replacement Component. If the Participating Co-Tenant(s) holding more than fifty percent (50%) of the Proportionate Shares fail(s) to approve such a proposed Alternative Replacement Component within thirty (30) days of receipt of the Replacement Notice, the Shared Facilities Manager shall install the Proposed Replacement Component; provided, however, that if within thirty (30) days of receipt of the Replacement Notice, Participating Co-Tenant(s) holding more than fifty percent (50%) of the Proportionate Shares notifies the Shared Facilities Manager not to install the Proposed Replacement Component, the Shared Facilities Manager shall not proceed with the installation thereof, unless and until the Shared Facilities Manager is required to replace such component due to an Emergency, in which event the Shared Facilities Manager shall proceed with the replacement of the component with the Proposed Replacement Component. (c) If any Proposed Replacement Component or Alternate Replacement Component is not approved in accordance with Section 1.5(b), either Participating Co-Tenant shall have an option to procure the Proposed Replacement Component at its cost and expense. Such Participating Co-Tenant shall indemnify the other Participating Co-Tenant for any costs and losses resulting from procurement and installation of such Proposed Replacement Component. (d) Conditions to Installation of Replacement Component. If the Shared Facilities Manager installs a Replacement Component, it shall (i) limit, to the extent commercially reasonable and subject to Good Utility Practice, any interference with the use by the Co-Tenants of the Shared Facilities during construction activities, and (ii) except in the event of an Emergency, (A) schedule during an off-peak and/or low generation down-time period any required disconnection of the Shared Facilities to conduct construction activities in order to minimize the impact on the Projects of the Co-Tenants, and (B) provide at least thirty (30) days' prior written notice of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof. The Participating Co-Tenant in the Shared Facilities in which the Replacement Component is installed shall indemnify and hold harmless the other Co-Tenant from all claims and damages, including third party liability claims, property and revenue losses (if any), incurred as a result of the construction or installation of a Replacement Component, to the extent that such claims and damages are not covered by the insurance required by the provisions of Article 6. 1.6 Additional Facilities. The Initial Shared Facilities are sufficient for the construction, operation, and maintenance of the Don A. Campbell 1 Project. To the extent that any additional facilities, improvements, modifications, or upgrades of facilities (the "Additional Facilities") or any additional property rights, easements, leases or licenses ("Additional Land Rights") are required for the transmission of electricity from any Additional Project to the Interconnection Point or to the interconnection of such Additional Project (or additions thereto) with the Transmitting Utility, the Co-Tenant owning such Additional Project shall be solely responsible for the cost and expense of procurement and installation of, and capital expenditures related to, such Additional Facilities and Additional Land Rights. The Additional Facilities and Additional Land Rights shall be (i) procured by the Co-Tenant owning such Additional Project for and on behalf of itself and the other Co-Tenant intending to use such Additional Facilities and Additional Land Rights, and (ii) if such Additional Facilities and Additional Land Rights will be utilized by both of the Co-Tenants, added as Shared Facilities or Shared Premises hereunder, held in undivided ownership interests in accordance with each Co-Tenant's Undivided Interest and deemed Shared Facilities or Shared Premises hereunder and be incorporated into, and governed by, the terms hereof. All Additional Facilities and Additional Land Rights shall be and remain free of any lien or encumbrance, except as permitted under this Agreement. Upon the installation of Additional Facilities that constitute Shared Facilities (a) no Co-Tenant will directly or indirectly, commence, maintain, support or join in any action or proceedings of any kind to partition the Shared Facilities, the Shared Premises, the Undivided Transmission Line Grant or any interest therein or portion thereof, and (b) upon the procurement of Additional Land Rights that constitute Shared Premises hereunder pursuant to this Section 1.6, the Shared Facilities Manager shall prepare amendments to Exhibits A and D to reflect the addition of the Additional Land Rights and Additional Facilities which shall be submitted to and signed by the Co-Tenants as provided in Section 4.6 below. 1.7 Conditions to Installation of Additional Facilities. Either Co-Tenant installing Additional Facilities shall (i) not unreasonably interfere with the use by any other Co-Tenant of the Shared Facilities or the use by ORNI 47 of the Don A. Campbell 1 Project Facilities, (ii) to the extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak and/or low generation down-time period any required disconnection of the Shared Facilities to conduct construction activities in order to minimize the impact on the Projects of the other Co-Tenant, (iii) provide at least thirty (30) days' prior written notice of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, (iv) take into consideration, to the extent commercially reasonable, any changes in the construction plans or timing of construction requested in writing by the other Co-Tenant, provided that the other Co-Tenant shall not attempt to interfere with the installation of the proposed Additional Facilities, unless such installation can reasonably be expected to result in an Emergency or violate the terms of any Transmission Line Agreement, this Agreement, or any Interconnection Agreement, and (v) provided further that the installing Co-Tenant shall indemnify and hold harmless the other Co-Tenant from all claims and damages, including third party claims, property and revenue losses incurred, as a result of such construction activities, to the extent such claims and damages are not covered by the insurance required by Article 6. 1.8 Warranty Claims. ORNI 47 (with respect to the Initial Shared Facilities), and the Shared Facilities Manager or either Co-Tenant installing any Replacement Component or Additional Facilities (with respect to such facilities) shall: (i) exercise such Co-Tenant s rights under the subcontractor and vendor warranties with respect to the Shared Facilities, Replacement Component or Additional Facilities, as applicable; (ii) monitor and report to the other Co-Tenant concerning the remaining terms of any warranties on the Shared Facilities, Replacement Component or Additional Facilities, as applicable; (iii) perform such inspections as are reasonable to ensure that any final warranty work is not required prior to the expiration of any such warranty, and (iv) prepare and prosecute warranty claims, if reasonably necessary to enforce any such warranties. 1.9 Statement of Intent of Co-Tenants. The arrangement and ownership structure contemplated by this Agreement is not being made with the intention or expectation of producing revenue or making or sharing in any profits from the operation of the Shared Facilities, but merely as a form of legal ownership whereby the Co-Tenants can accomplish their respective objectives of independently owning and operating their respective Undivided Interests in the Shared Facilities in connection with their respective Projects, subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement. 1.10 Maintenance of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant. Each Co-Tenant that is a party thereto shall be responsible for maintaining the Undivided Transmission Line Grant in full force and effect, and each Co-Tenant shall be responsible for not violating the terms of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant. Any amounts due under the terms of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant shall be shared in accordance with Article 2 below. If either Co-Tenant fails to pay its Proportionate Share of amounts due under the terms of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant, the Shared Facilities Manager may pay such amount, subject to reimbursement from the Co-Tenant(s) in accordance with Article 2 below. 1.11 Control of Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in this Agreement, the Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager hereby clarify and affirm their intent that, until the Don A. Campbell 2 Project achieves Substantial Completion, ORNI 47 shall be the sole Co-Tenant to have the right to control the use of the Shared Premises, the Shared Facilities and the Undivided Transmission Line Grant for the transmission of electric energy and the operation of any communications facilities. 1.12 Effective Date. This Agreement shall become effective on the date ( Effective Date ) on which this Agreement shall be executed and delivered by or on behalf of each of the Parties, all Regulatory Contract Approvals have been obtained by each Party, all required approvals and grants by the United States Bureau of Land Management have been obtained for the Undivided Interest of ORNI 47 and the Undivided Interest of ORNI 37, respectively, with respect to the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises, and the LGI Co-Tenancy Agreement and the FA&R LGIA, respectively, shall be effective in accordance with their terms. ARTICLE 2 ALLOCATION AND PAYMENT OF EXPENSES AND COSTS 2.1 Undivided Transmission Line Grant and Initial Shared Facilities. ORNI 47 shall be responsible for and pay all costs and expenses relating to the negotiation and procurement of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant and the engineering, procurement, installation and construction of the Initial Shared Facilities. 2.2 Additional Facilities. The Co-Tenant (or Co-Tenants, if the Additional Facilities are being acquired at the joint expense of two or more Co-Tenants) installing the Additional Facilities shall be responsible for and pay all costs and expenses relating to the engineering, procurement, installation, and construction of the Additional Facilities and for the procurement of any Additional Land Rights. 2.3 Maintenance and Repair of Shared Facilities and Shared Premises. Each Co-Tenant shall be responsible for and shall pay, in accordance with Exhibit B attached hereto, its Proportionate Share of the Fixed Fee and other expenses and liabilities relating to the use, inspection, maintenance, repair and replacement of the Shared Premises, Undivided Transmission Line Grant and Shared Facilities and all other fees, expenses and liabilities associated with the Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities and incurred in accordance with this Agreement (collectively, the "Shared O&M Expenses"), beginning on the Effective Date for ORNI 47 and on the Substantial Completion Date of each Additional Project for the Co-Tenant owning or operating such Additional Project. 2.4 Invoicing, Late Payments. The Shared Facilities Manager shall be responsible for invoicing the Co-Tenants for their respective Proportionate Share of the Shared O&M Expenses by the fifteenth (15th) day of each month, which shall be payable within fifteen (15) days after receipt of an invoice from the Shared Facilities Manager setting forth the amount that is due. All sums not paid within thirty (30) days after receipt of such an invoice shall thereafter bear interest at the Default Interest Rate. Each Participating Co-Tenant shall have the right to audit, and receive (and the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide) supporting documentation for, any expenses or other amounts required to be paid by such Participating Co-Tenant hereunder. 2.5 Ad Valorem Taxes and Assessments. (a) Each Co-Tenant shall pay all ad valorem taxes and assessments that are assessed to such Co-Tenant as a result of its ownership of its Undivided Interests in the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises. If the Co-Tenants are not separately assessed for their ownership interests in the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises, then the Shared Facilities Manager shall pay such taxes and assessments prior to delinquency and shall allocate the full taxes and assessments in an equitable manner in accordance with each Co-Tenant's Undivided Interests and notify the Co-Tenants of such allocation, in which case each Co-Tenant shall be obligated to reimburse the Shared Facilities Manager for a portion of such ad valorem taxes and assessments based on the Shared Facility Manager's allocation. Any increased ad valorem taxes resulting from Additional Facilities that are added as Shared Facilities hereunder or Additional Land Rights that are added as Shared Premises hereunder shall be the responsibility of the Co-Tenant or Co-Tenants installing such Additional Facilities or procuring such Additional Land Rights. (b) Each Co-Tenant shall have the right, in its sole discretion, to contest by legal proceedings (which may be brought in the name(s) of each Co-Tenant where appropriate or required), the validity or amount of any assessments or taxes for which such Co-Tenant is responsible hereunder. Each Co-Tenant shall in all respects cooperate with each other Co-Tenant in any such contest; provided, however, that the contesting Co-Tenant shall promptly reimburse each such Co-Tenant for any costs or fees incurred during such cooperation. 2.6 Costs of Maintenance and Repair Work. (a) The Shared Facilities Manager shall perform all ordinary and routine repairs and maintenance of the Shared Facilities for the Fixed Fee. (b) For any Major Maintenance Work included in any Shared Facilities O&M Budget or work necessary to respond to an Emergency, the Shared Facilities Manager shall be reimbursed for the actual costs of such work or services provided by the Shared Facilities Manager plus a ten percent (10%) mark-up for procurement-related costs and labor-related costs of all items incurred by or on behalf of the Shared Facilities Manager in connection with the performance of such Major Maintenance Work or work responding to an Emergency. Such costs reimbursable under this Section 2.6(b) shall be reimbursed by each Participating Co-Tenant based on such Participating Co-Tenant's Proportionate Share within thirty (30) days after written request by the Shared Facilities Manager (which shall include copies of all relevant invoices for such work). 2.7 Shared Facilities O&M Budget. (a) Upon the Effective Date and at least forty-five (45) days prior to the beginning of each calendar year thereafter during the term hereof, the Shared Facilities Manager shall prepare and submit to the Participating Co-Tenants a proposed budget for the operation, maintenance and repair of the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises for the following calendar year, or the portions of the calendar year remaining after the execution of this Agreement (each, a "Shared Facilities O&M Budget"), which budget shall include the estimated cost of anticipated repairs and capital expenditures and the Fixed Fee and reimbursable costs (to be paid to the Shared Facilities Manager) contemplated in this Agreement for anticipated operation and maintenance services and repairs to be provided by the Shared Facilities Manager during each month of the following calendar year (or, as to the initial Shared Facilities O&M Budget, during each month of the calendar year in which the Effective Date occurs), including any Shared O&M Expenses. The Shared Facilities O&M Budget shall set forth the respective amounts allocated to the different Co-Tenants in accordance with Exhibit B attached hereto. When approved pursuant to subparagraph (b) below, the Shared Facilities O&M Budget shall be the "Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget" for such year. (b) The Participating Co-Tenants shall give their approval or disapproval of the Shared Facilities O&M Budget no later than thirty (30) days after receipt thereof from the Shared Facilities Manager. If any Participating Co-Tenant objects to all or any portion of the proposed Shared Facilities O&M Budget, such Participating Co-Tenant shall furnish the Shared Facilities Manager in writing the reasons for such objections and shall immediately begin discussions with the Shared Facilities Manager in an effort to reach a mutually agreeable Shared Facilities O&M Budget. Upon such agreement, the Shared Facilities Manager shall revise the Shared Facilities O&M Budget with respect thereto. If the Shared Facilities O&M Budget is approved by Participating Co-Tenants holding at least fifty percent (50%) of the Proportionate Shares the Shared Facilities O&M Budget will be the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget for the following calendar year. If Participating Co-Tenants holding at least fifty percent (50%) of the Proportionate Shares do not approve the proposed Shared Facilities O&M Budget, the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget for the previous calendar year (or the last Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget if the Shared Facilities O&M Budget for the prior year was not approved) shall apply, provided that any single extraordinary expense (other than as required in an Emergency) in excess of ten percent (10%) of the last Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget shall not be incurred without the prior approval of the Participating Co-Tenants holding a majority of the Proportionate Shares. 2.8 Other Expenses Caused By Co-Tenants. Notwithstanding the provisions of this Agreement, any costs, claims, loss or other liability arising from the actions or inactions of a Co-Tenant in violation or breach of the covenants herein or the provisions of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant shall be the responsibility of such Co-Tenant, and the responsible Co-Tenant shall fully indemnify and defend the other Co-Tenant against such costs, claims, losses and liabilities, except to the extent caused by any Indemnified Party hereunder. 2.9 Rights of Other Co-Tenant for Non-Payment. If either Co-Tenant (a "Non-Paying Co-Tenant") fails to timely pay any amount due from such Co-Tenant under this Agreement, any other Co-Tenant or the Shared Facilities Manager may (but is not obligated to) make such payment on behalf of such Non-Paying Co-Tenant and the amount so paid shall be immediately due and payable from the Non-Paying Co-Tenant to such other Co-Tenant or the Shared Facilities Manager, together with interest from the date paid at the Default Interest Rate. Such remedy shall be in addition to the right of such other Co-Tenant or the Shared Facilities Manager to pursue any other remedies that may be available to it under applicable law. 2.10 Liens. No Co-Tenant shall, directly or indirectly, create, incur or permit to exist any lien on the Shared Facilities, the Shared Premises, the Undivided Transmission Line Grant, or the Undivided Interest of any other Co-Tenant, including but not limited to any lien for unpaid taxes, any judgment lien or any mechanic s or materialmen s lien, except in accordance with this Agreement. If any such lien attaches or a Co-Tenant receives notice of any such lien, the Co-Tenant whose actual or alleged act or omission resulted in such lien shall cause such lien to be released and removed of record within fifteen (15) days of such attachment or notice, unless (a) such Co-Tenant (i) in good faith contests or disputes the claim or claims of the lienholders and the validity of such liens, (ii) promptly commences legal action to remove such lien and (iii) furnishes to the other Co-Tenant a bond or other acceptable security in an amount sufficient to discharge all such contested liens and (b) during such period the lienholders proceedings are stayed. ARTICLE 3 OTHER RIGHTS AND OBLIGATIONS OF CO-TENANTS 3.1 Interconnection Rights. (a) Each Co-Tenant shall be responsible for entering into an Interconnection Agreement with the Transmitting Utility for the delivery of the full electric energy from its own Project to the Transmitting Utility at its respective Interconnection Point from the date of initial production of electric energy from such Project. (b) No Co-Tenant is providing any interconnection or transmission services to the other Co-Tenant under this Agreement, and no Co-Tenant shall have any obligation to the other Co-Tenant to provide any interconnection or related rights with a Transmitting Utility. (c) The Shared Facilities Manager shall act in the interests of the Participating Co-Tenants in complying with the provisions of the Interconnection Agreement. 3.2 Capacity of Projects. Campbell 2 Project following Substantial Completion thereof shall be the greater of (i) 22 MW and (ii) the electric generating facility capacity net at 1.0 pf set forth for Don A. Campbell 2 Project in Appendix A to the FA&R LGIA, as the same may be amended, in MW. In the event a Co-Tenant fails to so maintain its Project, which failure, in the reasonable judgment of the Shared Facilities Manager, does or may materially adversely affect the Shared Facilities the Shared Facilities Manager may, at its option, notify the defaulting Co-Tenant, and disconnect the defaulting Co-Tenant's Project in accordance with Section 4.5. Each Co-Tenant shall install a metering device at its Project reasonably acceptable to the Shared Facilities Manager and shall permit the Shared Facilities Manager to read the results of such metering device upon reasonable prior notice from the Shared Facilities Manager. 3.5 Standard of Performance. The Shared Facilities Manager and each Co-Tenant shall cooperate in good faith with the other Co-Tenant and perform their obligations hereunder with respect to the Undivided Transmission Line Grant, the Shared Facilities and the Shared Premises (i) in accordance with this Agreement, all Governmental Requirements, Good Utility Practice, the Interconnection Agreement, and the terms of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant, and (ii) in a manner that is (A) non-discriminatory, and (B) attempts to maximize the delivery of energy from the Projects at a reasonable cost. In addition, the Shared Facilities Manager shall endeavor to perform its obligations hereunder in compliance with the Interconnection Agreement; provided that the Co-Tenants shall deliver to the Shared Facilities Manager a copy of the Interconnection Agreement. To the extent that the Shared Facilities Manager's obligations hereunder are materially increased in order to comply with the Interconnection Agreement, the Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager shall negotiate an equitable adjustment to the Fixed Fee, and the Co-Tenant causing such increase and adjustment shall be solely responsible for the payment of such increase in the Fixed Fee. 3.6 Co-Tenant Representatives. THE FOREGOING EXCLUSION OF ALL WARRANTIES BY EACH CO-TENANT INCLUDES EXCLUSION OF IMPLIED WARRANTIES OF SUITABILITY AND FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE. 3.8 Specific Performance. Each of the Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager on behalf of the Co-Tenants shall have the right to seek specific performance of any of the obligations of a defaulting Co-Tenant hereunder, including the right to enforce a transfer of any of the defaulting Co-Tenant s Undivided Interests hereunder. 3.9 Withdrawal if Don A. Campbell 2 Project Not Completed. If ORNI 37 determines that it will not construct the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, ORNI 37 shall have the right to withdraw from this Agreement, provided written notice thereof is given to ORNI 47. Within thirty (30) days after the achievement of Substantial Completion of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, and thereafter on each January 1st, ORNI 37 shall pay to ORNI 47 the amount of One Thousand Dollars ($1,000) per MW for the Don A. Campbell 2 Project's Net Rated Capacity (the "Reimbursement Payment"). Reimbursement Payments for partial calendar years shall be prorated. 3.11 Capacity on Shared Facilities. ORNI 47 shall at all times retain a right to the capacity available on the Shared Facilities to the full extent required in order for ORNI 47 to operate the Don A. Campbell 1 Project at its full capacity, to transmit the entire energy output of the Don A. Campbell 1 Project to its interconnection with Sierra Pacific Power Company d/b/a NV Energy, and to sell all other products produced by the Don A. Campbell 1 Project in the relevant markets. ORNI 37 shall obtain any approvals necessary for the Don A. Campbell 2 Project from the United States Bureau of Land Management. ARTICLE 4 MANAGEMENT RIGHTS AND VOTING 4.1 In General. Except as expressly stated herein, all decisions with respect to the Undivided Transmission Line Grant (but only with respect to the use, operation, construction, repair, replacement, maintenance or removal of the Shared Facilities) or the Shared Facilities, as well as any actions to implement this Agreement, shall be taken by the Shared Facilities Manager, which, except as expressly stated herein, shall have full authority to act on behalf of the Co-Tenants with respect to all matters relating to the Undivided Transmission Line Grant (but only with respect to the use, operation, construction, repair, maintenance, replacement, or removal of the Shared Facilities) or the Shared Facilities. The Co-Tenants shall not participate or interfere in the management of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant (with respect to the use, operation, construction, repair, maintenance, replacement, or removal of the Shared Facilities) or the Shared Facilities in any way except as expressly otherwise stated herein. Each Co-Tenant shall have the right to manage and otherwise deal with its respective rights and obligations under the Undivided Transmission Line Grant in accordance with the terms of this Agreement and except as provided in this Section 4.1. 4.2 Specific Authority. Without limiting the generality of the foregoing, but subject to Section 4.3 the Shared Facilities Manager shall have the power, without further consent or approval of the Co-Tenants: (a) To negotiate, enter into, execute, acknowledge or amend agreements relating to the use, operation, maintenance, construction, replacement, and repair of the Shared Facilities (as permitted by this Agreement) on behalf of the Co-Tenants, subject in all cases to the provisions of Section 1.5 and provided that (i) no such action(s) adversely affect the rights or privileges of either Co-Tenant except with respect to incurring additional expenses for the accounts of the Co-Tenants permitted under Section 1.5 and (ii) the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide each Co-Tenant with copies of any such agreement promptly upon execution thereof; (b) To employ from time to time, at the expense of the Co-Tenants and in accordance with the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget or as otherwise required in an Emergency, persons, firms or corporations to render services generally needed to accomplish the purposes of the Co-Tenants with respect to the Shared Premises, the Shared Facilities or this Agreement, provided that if the Shared Facilities Manager retains any Affiliate of the Shared Facilities Manager for any of these purposes, the fees charged shall be based on the fair market value for similar services, and the Shared Facilities Manager shall not be entitled to the percentage mark-up set forth in Section 2.6; (c) To pay and collect amounts due in connection with the Shared Facilities in accordance with the terms of this Agreement, and to maintain one or more bank accounts wherein funds received by the Shared Facilities Manager in connection with its duties hereunder shall be maintained; (d) To expend monies necessary for the management, operation, maintenance, and repair of the Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities in accordance with the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget or as otherwise required in an Emergency; (e) To negotiate with, and represent the Co-Tenants interests before any Governmental Authority regarding property valuation and real property taxes (if any) related to the Undivided Transmission Line Grant (but only with respect to the use, operation, construction, repair, maintenance, replacement or removal of the Shared Facilities), the Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities; (f) To commit to the expenditure of or spend such amounts for and on behalf of the Co-Tenants as are reasonably necessary to expedite repairs to the Shared Premises or the Shared Facilities due to an Emergency; provided that the Shared Facilities Manager gives notice concurrently or as soon thereafter as reasonably practical by facsimile to the Co-Tenants regarding the nature and amount of the expenditures; and (g) To execute, acknowledge, and deliver any and all instruments and take such other steps as are reasonably necessary to effectuate the foregoing and as are consistent therewith. 4.3 Limitation on Authority. (a) Notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained herein, the Shared Facilities Manager shall not, without the approval of both of the Co-Tenants: (1) Create, permit or cause to be created any lien or encumbrance on any Shared Premises, the Undivided Transmission Line Grant or the Shared Facilities; (2) Amend, modify or terminate the terms of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant; (3) Perform or omit to perform any act which would cause any person reasonably to believe that the Shared Facilities Manager is a partner of the Co-Tenants or authorized to bind the Co-Tenants, except as expressly provided herein; (4) Sell, assign, mortgage, encumber, pledge, convey or otherwise transfer all or any portion of the Undivided Interests held by either Co-Tenant, or any interest or estate in, to or under the Undivided Transmission Line Grant or in or to any component of the Shared Facilities (other than due to obsolescence or upon winding up hereunder in accordance with Section 8.4); (5) Borrow funds on behalf of either Co-Tenant; or (6) Procure any insurance coverage that is less than the coverages required by Article 6 hereof. (b) The Shared Facilities Manager shall not, without the approval of all of the Participating Co-Tenants: (1) Compromise or settle (i) any single claim, demand, class action proceeding, or debt in which the amount of damages is in excess of One Hundred Thousand Dollars ($100,000), or (ii) claims, demands, class action proceedings or debt in which the aggregate amount of damages during any calendar year is in excess of Two Hundred Thousand Dollars ($200,000); or (2) Subject to Section 4.2(f), incur or consent to incur cumulative expenses of more than ten percent (10%) of the aggregate amount of the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget in any calendar year (exclusive of the Fixed Fee) that are not included in the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget or incurred for the installation of a Replacement Component as authorized under Section 1.5. 4.4 Curtailment of Delivery. The Shared Facilities Manager may, in accordance with the following provisions, direct the Co-Tenants to interrupt or reduce deliveries of electrical power (i) when necessary in order to maintain, repair, replace, remove, investigate, inspect or test any part of the Shared Facilities; (ii) if the Shared Facilities Manager determines, in its reasonable discretion, that interruption or reduction is necessary due to an Emergency; or (iii) at the direction of (A) the Transmitting Utility pursuant to the Transmitting Utility s rights under an Interconnection Agreement or (B) any regional transmission organization. With respect to any interruption or reduction of deliveries of electrical power pursuant to clauses (i) or (ii) of the preceding sentence, the Shared Facilities Manager shall limit the length of any such interruption or curtailment to that time strictly necessary to correct the problem. Any interruption or curtailment made pursuant to clause (i) above shall be made to the extent commercially reasonable. Unless directed otherwise by a regional transmission organization or a Transmitting Utility, the Shared Facilities Manager shall curtail each Co-Tenant as follows: in the event of any curtailment at the direction of the Transmitting Utility, such curtailment shall be allocated first to ORNI 37 according to its Proportionate Share; and ORNI 47 shall not be curtailed unless and until such curtailment at the direction of the Transmitting Utility exceeds ORNI 37 s Proportionate Share; provided however, if (a) the need for the interruption or reduction can in accordance with Good Utility Practice be attributed to a particular Co-Tenant s Project or portions of its Project, then the Shared Facilities Manager shall, allocate such interruption or reduction to such Project, or (b) a different allocation is necessary to comply with the FA&R LGIA or the Transmitting Utility direction pursuant to the FA&R LGIA, then the Shared Facilities Manager shall allocate such interruption or reduction in accordance with the FA&R LGIA or the Transmission Utility s direction, as applicable. Each Co-Tenant shall promptly effect such interruption in, or reduction of, delivery as the Shared Facilities Manager shall direct pursuant to this Section 4.4 upon notice from the Shared Facilities Manager, which notice shall be reasonable under the circumstances. In the event notice is impracticable or a Co-Tenant fails to promptly comply therewith, the Shared Facilities Manager may effect the same by direct action. 4.5 Disconnection of Shared Facilities. The Shared Facilities Manager shall have the power and authority to disconnect a Project (a) if the Shared Facilities Manager determines, in its reasonable discretion, that disconnection is necessary in the event of an Emergency, or (b) at the direction of the Transmitting Utility pursuant to rights under any Interconnection Agreement. In the cases of (i) a real or reasonably perceived Emergency as described in clause (a) or (ii) as directed under clause (b) above, the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide notice to the relevant Co-Tenant concurrently with disconnection of its Project or as soon as thereafter as is reasonably practical. In the case of a failure by a Co-Tenant to maintain its Project as required under Section 3.4, the Shared Facilities Manager shall provide at least thirty (30) days' advance written notice to the relevant Co-Tenant and its Secured Party prior to disconnecting its Project in order for such Co-Tenant to cure any failure. Any Project disconnected shall be reconnected when the specific default is cured in full. The Shared Facilities Manager and each of the Co-Tenants will accept substitute performance necessary to cure the default in full that is tendered by a Secured Party to cure the breach or default of such Co-Tenant. 4.6 Changes in Proportionate Shares. The Proportionate Shares shall be modified by the Shared Facilities Manager from time to time to reflect (i) confirmation of the Net Rated Capacity of a Project, upon the Substantial Completion of a Project, (ii) increases in the Net Rated Capacity of a Project as permitted herein or otherwise agreed upon by both of the Co-Tenants, (iii) additional Co-Tenants becoming parties to this Agreement in accordance with the provisions of Section 7.2; (iv) in the case of ORNI 37, the commencement of ORNI 37's use of the Shared Facilities following Substantial Completion of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, and (v) the withdrawal of a Co-Tenant in accordance with Section 8.3. Any changes in the Shared Facilities and the Proportionate Shares shall be evidenced by an amendment to Exhibit B, prepared by the Shared Facilities Manager and submitted to each Co-Tenant and attached hereto. 4.7 Voting or Approval Rights. Unless specifically provided elsewhere in this Agreement, each Co-Tenant shall have the right to vote or give its approval, in proportion to its Proportionate Share, on any matter requiring or needing a vote or approval of the Co-Tenants. A Co-Tenant may not vote any increase in its Proportionate Share until such increase has been approved by those Co-Tenants whose Projects have achieved Substantial Completion; provided, however, until such increase has been approved by the other Co-Tenant, such Co-Tenant shall not be responsible for any increased expenses due to such increase in the Co-Tenant's Proportionate Share. 4.8 Shared Facilities Manager Representative. On or promptly after the Effective Date, the Shared Facilities Manager shall, by written notice to the Co-Tenants, designate an individual representative (the "Shared Facilities Manager Representative") whose instructions, requests, and decisions will be binding upon such Shared Facilities Manager in all matters concerning this Agreement, except that the Shared Facilities Manager Representative shall not have the authority to amend this Agreement. The Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right to change the Shared Facilities Manager Representative at any time and from time to time by written notice to the Co-Tenants. 4.9 Competing Ventures. Any party hereto (including the Shared Facilities Manager) may engage in or possess an interest in other business ventures of any nature and description, independently or with others, including but not limited to the ownership, financing, leasing, management, syndication, investment, brokerage and development of real property (including real property of the same type and nature as the Projects), and no party shall have any right by virtue of this Agreement in and to such independent ventures or to the income or profits derived therefrom. ARTICLE 5 SHARED FACILITIES MANAGER 5.1 Appointment of the Shared Facilities Manager. Ormat Nevada Inc. shall be the Shared Facilities Manager as of the Effective Date and shall hold such position until it (i) resigns, (ii) is terminated for cause, or (iii) is replaced by the Participating Co-Tenants who hold, in the aggregate, in excess of fifty percent 50% of the Proportionate Shares. If ORNI 37 has commenced and is diligently prosecuting construction of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, a replacement of Ormat Nevada Inc. under clause (iii) above may only be effected after the Substantial Completion of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, unless ORNI 37 shall be in default under its power purchase agreement and the buyer under such power purchase agreement shall have exercised its right to terminate the power purchase agreement. 5.2 Liability. The Shared Facilities Manager shall not be liable, responsible or accountable in damages or otherwise to either Co-Tenant for any act performed in good faith by the Shared Facilities Manager in the discharge of its duties hereunder as the Shared Facilities Manager or in the exercise of its powers and authority hereunder as the Shared Facilities Manager, including, without limitation, damages arising out of the disconnection of, or the election not to disconnect, a Co-Tenant s Project from the Shared Facilities, unless the acts or omissions of the Shared Facilities Manager constitute a material breach by the Shared Facilities Manager of this Agreement, fraud, willful misconduct, or gross negligence. In no event shall the Shared Facilities Manager's aggregate liability in any calendar year under, in connection with or arising from, this Agreement (other than liability arising out of the fraud, willful misconduct or gross negligence of the Shared Facilities Manager), whether regarding any indemnification, environmental responsibility or otherwise, exceed the amount of the annual Fixed Fee paid to the Shared Facilities Manager under this Agreement for such calendar year (the Maximum Liability ); provided, however, that the preceding limitation shall not in any way limit the amounts recoverable under any existing insurance policy. Amounts recovered under any existing insurance policy may not be claimed from the Shared Facilities Manager under this Agreement; provided, however, that such amounts recovered shall not otherwise reduce the Maximum Liability. 5.3 Removal of the Shared Facilities Manager. The Shared Facilities Manager may be removed, as set forth in this Section 5.3. (a) Removal for Cause. The Shared Facilities Manager may be removed for cause by any Participating Co-Tenant, provided that each of the following conditions is satisfied: (i) The Shared Facilities Manager has defaulted on its obligations under this Agreement. (ii) The Participating Co-Tenant(s) seeking removal of the Shared Facilities Manager for cause has/have provided written notice (the "Default Notice") to the Shared Facilities Manager and the other Co-Tenant of the default by the Shared Facilities Manager hereunder. Such notice shall contain a general description of the facts and circumstances giving rise to the default. (iii) The Shared Facilities Manager has failed, within fifteen (15) days of the delivery of the Default Notice to cure a payment default, or thirty (30) days after delivery of the Default Notice to cure any other default described in such Default Notice; provided that, if a default (other than a payment default) is not reasonably capable of being cured within thirty (30) days and such default is capable of cure, then the Shared Facilities Manager shall have an additional period of time to cure such default, but in no event more than ninety (90) days from the delivery of the Default Notice. (b) Disputes. If any Participating Co-Tenant delivers a Default Notice pursuant to Section 5.3(a) and the Shared Facilities Manager disputes such default, then the following procedures shall apply: (i) Within five (5) days after delivery of such notice from such Participating Co-Tenant, the Shared Facilities Manager shall deliver to the Participating Co-Tenants a notice with a detailed description of the reasons the Shared Facilities Manager disputes such default, and within five (5) days after delivery of such notice by the Shared Facilities Manager, the Participating Co-Tenant seeking removal and the Shared Facilities Manager shall meet and confer in good faith with respect to such default and the cure for such default. Such meeting and conference may be done either by telephone or in person. (ii) If, after the meeting and conference referred to in Section 5.3(b)(i), the Shared Facilities Manager and the Participating Co-Tenant seeking removal cannot agree on whether a default exists, then such dispute shall be submitted to dispute resolution pursuant to Section 12.2. (c) Removal Without Cause. The Shared Facilities Manager may be removed without cause and a new Shared Facilities Manager may be elected upon a written vote of the Participating Co-Tenants who hold, in the aggregate, in excess of fifty percent (50%) of the Proportionate Shares; provided that if ORNI 37 has commenced and is diligently prosecuting construction of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, removal of Ormat Nevada Inc. as Shared Facilities Manager may only be effected after the Substantial Completion of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, unless ORNI 37 shall be in default under its power purchase agreement and the buyer under such power purchase agreement shall have exercised its right to terminate the power purchase agreement. No vote to remove a Shared Facilities Manager shall be effective unless coupled with the election of another Co-Tenant or third party manager as the new Shared Facilities Manager, who agrees so to act. (f) Resignation. The Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right to resign as the Shared Facilities Manager upon sixty (60) days' notice to the Co-Tenants. (a) Maintenance or Records. The Shared Facilities Manager shall maintain books and records in sufficient detail to verify amounts incurred by the Shared Facilities Manager and/or due and payable hereunder for a period of not less than three (3) years after the end of the calendar month to which they relate or such longer period as may be required by applicable law, and all such books and records shall be available for inspection and/or copying by each Co-Tenant or its authorized representative at the cost and expense of such Co-Tenant and at reasonable times during regular business hours, upon reasonable notice to the Shared Facilities Manager. (b) Provision of Records. The Shared Facilities Manager shall provide quarterly reports to the Co-Tenants sufficient to keep the Co-Tenants reasonably apprised as to significant matters concerning the maintenance and repair of Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities, including such matters related thereto as may have a material impact on the operation, maintenance and repair of each Co-Tenant s Project. 5.5 Shared Facilities Manager Fees. (a) As consideration for the management and routine maintenance services to be performed hereunder, the Shared Facilities Manager shall be paid an annual fixed operation fee of Eight Thousand Three Hundred Thirty-Three Dollars ($8,333), and upon the Substantial Completion of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project, an additional Eight Thousand Three Hundred Thirty-Three Dollars ($8,333) per year for such Don A. Campbell 2 Project (the "Fixed Fee"), payable monthly in equal installments, in advance, beginning on Substantial Completion of the Don A. Campbell 2 Project and continuing on the first day of each calendar month. (b) The Fixed Fee shall be subject to good faith renegotiation every five (5) years. The Fixed Fee shall be allocated to the Co-Tenants equally on a per capita basis. The Fixed Fee may also be adjusted, by mutual agreement of the applicable Co-Tenants, in the event that any additional duties are added hereunder or in the event that amendments to this Agreement materially increase the scope of the Shared Facilities Manager s work. (c) The Fixed Fee shall cover the direct cost of labor employed by or on behalf of the Shared Facilities Manager for the routine operation and maintenance of the Shared Facilities (which specifically excludes labor in performing Major Maintenance Work or responding to an Emergency), and of administration of the Shared Facilities, including contract management services, procurement services and accounting support. (d) In addition to the Fixed Fee, but only to the extent included in the Approved Shared Facilities O&M Budget, the Shared Facilities Manager shall be paid or reimbursed for costs and expenses pursuant to Section 2.6(b) above. 5.6 Invoices. The Shared Facilities Manager shall have the right to pre-invoice the Co-Tenants for any materials and components for which the Shared Facilities Manager is entitled to reimbursement pursuant to Section 2.6(b) above, and not to proceed with the acquisition of such materials and components unless payment has been received by the Shared Facilities Manager for such materials and components, except that the Shared Facilities Manager shall not delay proceeding with such acquisition of materials or components in the event of an Emergency. ARTICLE 6 INSURANCE 6.1 Property Insurance. Each Co-Tenant shall arrange for and maintain its own property and extended coverage insurance (including coverage for its own business interruption losses) with respect to such Co-Tenant's respective Undivided Interest in the Shared Facilities. The property and extended coverage insurance shall be in an amount sufficient to pay such Co-Tenant's Proportionate Share of the costs and expenses to rebuild and replace the applicable Shared Facilities in the event of a casualty loss thereof or damage thereto. 6.2 Builder s All-Risk Insurance. Either Co-Tenant or the Shared Facilities Manager on behalf of the Co-Tenants constructing or installing any Replacement Components or Additional Facilities shall, during such construction or installation, maintain builder s all-risk insurance in an amount (i) sufficient to replace any part of the Shared Facilities, Replacement Components or Additional Facilities that may be affected by such construction, and (ii) that is reasonably acceptable to the Shared Facilities Manager. Such policies shall name the Shared Facilities Manager (to the extent of its insurable interest), Co-Tenants and their Secured Parties as additional insureds. 6.3 Liability Insurance. Each of the Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager (for no additional consideration) shall maintain liability insurance covering its respective activities on or with respect to the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises, including general liability coverage. Each Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager (for no additional consideration) shall obtain and maintain comprehensive general liability insurance covering liability for personal injury (including bodily injury and death), property damage to third parties, and damage to property of third parties in the care, custody and control of either Co-Tenant, the Shared Facilities Manager, and/or their respective employees in connection with operations at the Shared Facilities and Shared Premises with a combined single limit of not less than One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) per occurrence and Five Million Dollars ($5,000,000) annual aggregate for bodily injury and property damage, provided that such coverage (i) may be provided as part of a blanket policy covering other properties, (ii) shall comply with any statutory obligation imposed by workers compensation or occupational disease laws, (iii) shall contain a blanket broad form contractual endorsement and severability of interest clause, and (iv) shall designate the other Co-Tenant, the Shared Facilities Manager, the Secured Parties, and their officers, directors, employees and agents as additional insureds. If a policy described above is on a "claims made" basis, the retroactive date of the policy for ORNI 47 shall be the Effective Date. If a policy is on a "claims made" basis, such coverage shall survive the termination of this Agreement until the expiration of the maximum statutory period of limitations in the State of Nevada for actions based on contract or in tort. If coverage is on an "occurrence" basis, insurance on an occurrence basis shall be maintained for the term of this Agreement. 6.4 Workers Compensation. Each Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager (for no additional consideration) shall obtain and maintain minimum coverage to comply with any statutory obligation imposed by workers compensation or occupational disease laws for their employees. Additionally, each Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager (at no additional consideration) shall obtain employer's liability insurance for all its employees in the amount of $1,000,000 per accident. 6.5 Automobile Liability. The Shared Facilities Manager (at no additional consideration) shall also obtain and maintain an automobile liability insurance with a combined single limit of not less than One Million Dollars ($1,000,000) covering bodily injury and property damage, for hired, owned and non-owned vehicles. 6.6 Property Event. In the event of a covered property claim that affects any of the Shared Facilities, all insurance proceeds with respect to the Shared Facilities shall be pooled and applied to reconstruction of the affected Shared Facilities. If there is uninsured loss or insurance proceeds are inadequate, the Participating Co-Tenants shall contribute additional amounts based on the Proportionate Shares of the Participating Co-Tenants; provided that if either Co-Tenant fails to maintain insurance as required by this Agreement, such Co-Tenant shall be responsible for the portion of the loss for which insurance proceeds would have been available if such insurance had been maintained. 6.7 Form and Content of Insurance. All policies and binders with respect to insurance provided pursuant to this Article 6 shall be as follows: (a) Form of Policies. All insurance provided for hereunder shall be placed on forms reasonably acceptable to the Shared Facilities Manager, the Co-Tenants and the Secured Parties. (b) Insurance Companies. All insurance required hereunder shall be with insurers with an A.M. Best rating of A- or better or with insurers licensed to do business in Nevada and otherwise deemed acceptable to the Shared Facilities Manager, the Co-Tenants and the Secured Parties. (c) Severability. All liability insurance shall contain a severability of interest provision providing that, except with respect to the total limits of liability, the insurance shall apply to each insured or additional insured in the same manner as if separate policies had been issued to each. (d) Non-Recourse. All insurance shall provide that there will be no recourse against the additional insureds for the payment of premiums or commissions or (if such policies provide for the payment thereof) additional premiums or assessments. 6.8 Additional Requirements. (a) Waiver of Subrogation. All insurance maintained by the parties, with the exception of worker s compensation, shall provide for the waiver of any right of subrogation by the insurers thereunder against the other parties and the Secured Parties and their officers, directors, employees, agents and representatives, and any right of the insurers to any setoff or counterclaim or any other deduction, whether by attachment or otherwise, in respect of any liability of any such person insured under such policy. (b) Non-Vitiation. All insurance maintained by the Co-Tenants shall provide for the waiver of any right of the insurers to terminate, repudiate, rescind or avoid this insurance as against any insured or any agent of any insured on the grounds that the risk or claim was not adequately disclosed, or that it was in any way misrepresented, or increased, or that any term, condition or warranty was breached, or on the ground of negligence, unless deliberate or fraudulent non-disclosure or misrepresentation or breach by that insured is established in relation thereto. (c) Notice of Cancellation or Material Modification. All insurance shall provide that it may not be canceled or materially changed without giving the Shared Facilities Manager, the Co-Tenants and Secured Parties thirty (30) days' prior written notification thereof, except in cases of non-payment of premium for which ten (10) days' prior written notice shall be provided (unless a longer notice period for non-payment is agreed to by the relevant insurer). No later than the Effective Date each party shall furnish certificates of insurance to the other parties evidencing the insurance required pursuant to this Agreement and, if requested by any Secured Party, copies of the underlying insurance policies. The Co-Tenant maintaining any policy hereunder shall make all proofs of loss under such policy, and shall take all other action reasonably required to ensure collection from insurers for any loss under such policy, except that the other Co-Tenant shall cooperate and assist in the preparation of such proofs of loss and take such other actions on behalf of the Co-Tenants as may be requested by the Co-Tenants. (e) Payment of Deductibles and Self-Insured Retention Amounts. The maximum deductible or self-insured retention amount for any insurance coverage required to be carried hereunder shall be $500,000, unless agreed otherwise. Each Co-Tenant shall be responsible for deductibles or self-insured retention on any policy carried by it and, with respect to policies carried by the Shared Facilities Manager on behalf of both Co-Tenants, on a pro rata basis in proportion to the amount of each Co-Tenant s insurance recovery; provided, however, with respect to any claim under any policy provided by a Co-Tenant that results from the negligence of the Shared Facilities Manager, the Shared Facilities Manager shall be responsible for the payment of such deductible, to the extent of such negligence. (f) Subcontractor Insurance. The Shared Facilities Manager shall require all subcontractors to carry reasonably adequate coverage in accordance with the Shared Facilities Manager s normal practice, prior to entry on the Shared Premises and during the time in which they are engaged in performing services to be furnished by the Shared Facilities Manager. The Shared Facilities Manager shall provide the Co-Tenants, upon request, with acceptable evidence of any subcontractor s insurance evidencing such coverage. The Shared Facilities Manager shall not be responsible for payment of premiums and claims with respect to the insurance of either Co-Tenant's independent consultants, contractors and subcontractors. (g) Notification. The Co-Tenants and the Shared Facilities Manager agree to advise the other Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager as soon as practicable in writing of any notice of claim to which insurance pursuant to this Article 6 applies. (h) Self-help Rights. Should the Shared Facilities Manager or either Co-Tenant fail to provide or maintain any of the insurance policies required of it, either Co-Tenant (or its Secured Party) and, in the case of a Co-Tenant s failure, the Shared Facilities Manager, shall have the right to provide and/or maintain such coverage at such defaulting Co-Tenant s expense after a reasonable time to cure has passed. Any cost incurred by the Shared Facilities Manager or a Co-Tenant (or its Secured Party) in curing another Co-Tenant's default under this Section 6.8(h) shall be reimbursed by the defaulting Co-Tenant upon demand, together with interest at the Default Interest Rate until paid in full. No Co-Tenant shall be bound by any assignment, no assignment shall be valid, and no assignee of either Co-Tenant s Undivided Interest or rights under this Agreement shall become a Co-Tenant unless (i) all consents required under Section 7.1 have been obtained, (ii) all Governmental Requirements relating to such assignment have been complied with; (iii) the assignee will own and operate the Project of the assigning Co-Tenant; (iv) the assignee consents in writing to be bound by the terms of this Agreement in the place and stead of the assigning Co-Tenant, which written consent shall be in the form reasonably acceptable to such trustee, its successors and assigns; (v) the assignee assumes all of the Co-Tenant s obligations under the Undivided Transmission Line Grant and a counterpart of the assignment and assumption agreements, executed by such Co-Tenant and the assignee, in form satisfactory to the other Co-Tenant, is delivered to the other Co-Tenant, (vi) such assignment does not violate the terms of the Undivided Transmission Line Grant, (vii) such assignment does not violate the terms of the Don A. Campbell 1 PPA or the Proposed Don A. Campbell 2 PPA, as applicable, and (viii) any and all necessary Secured Party and other third party consents to such assignment have been obtained in writing and delivered to the other Co-Tenant and the Shared Facilities Manager. 7.3 Right to Encumber.
